862914274841665e-06, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this article\", \"from\": 21, \"to\": 33}, {\"ngram\": \"Images\", \"from\": 34, \"to\": 40}, {\"ngram\": \"the medal podium\", \"from\": 104, \"to\": 120}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Olympics\", \"from\": 180, \"to\": 197}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A frenzied debate has raged over the International Olympic Committee clearing the duo to compete in the women's boxing in Paris, despite them having been disqualified from last year's Women's World Championships for failing to meet eligibility criteria.\", \"from\": 201, \"to\": 454, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 238, \"end\": 269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 323, \"end\": 328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999988137103843, \"rank\": 1.1862914274841665e-06, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A frenzied debate\", \"from\": 201, \"to\": 218}, {\"ngram\": \"the duo\", \"from\": 279, \"to\": 286}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's boxing\", \"from\": 301, \"to\": 319}, {\"ngram\": \"last year's Women's World Championships\", \"from\": 373, \"to\": 412}, {\"ngram\": \"eligibility criteria\", \"from\": 433, \"to\": 453}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Amid the heat, science is shedding increasing light on our different chromosomal make-ups and what advantages they may bring to sport.\", \"from\": 456, \"to\": 590, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the heat\", \"from\": 461, \"to\": 469}, {\"ngram\": \"science\", \"from\": 471, \"to\": 478}, {\"ngram\": \"light\", \"from\": 502, \"to\": 507}, {\"ngram\": \"our different chromosomal make-ups\", \"from\": 511, \"to\": 545}, {\"ngram\": \"what advantages\", \"from\": 550, \"to\": 565}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 584, \"to\": 589}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the research is ongoing and even among the experts who spend their professional lives working on it, there are differing interpretations on what the science tells us.\", \"from\": 592, \"to\": 762, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the research\", \"from\": 596, \"to\": 608}, {\"ngram\": \"the experts\", \"from\": 635, \"to\": 646}, {\"ngram\": \"their professional lives\", \"from\": 657, \"to\": 681}, {\"ngram\": \"differing interpretations\", \"from\": 707, \"to\": 732}, {\"ngram\": \"the science\", \"from\": 741, \"to\": 752}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 759, \"to\": 761}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We do know that the process of sex determination starts when a foetus is developing.\", \"from\": 764, \"to\": 848, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the process\", \"from\": 780, \"to\": 791}, {\"ngram\": \"sex determination\", \"from\": 795, \"to\": 812}, {\"ngram\": \"a foetus\", \"from\": 825, \"to\": 833}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most females get two X chromosomes (XX), while most males get an X and a Y chromosome (XY).\", \"from\": 849, \"to\": 940, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 885, \"end\": 887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.6395136353696135e-73, \"text\": \"XX\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\"}, {\"begin\": 936, \"end\": 938, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phenotype\", \"score\": 0.9990347457424098, \"rank\": 0.000966186873838925, \"text\": \"XY\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phenotype\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phenotype\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Most females\", \"from\": 849, \"to\": 861}, {\"ngram\": \"two X chromosomes\", \"from\": 866, \"to\": 883}, {\"ngram\": \"most males\", \"from\": 896, \"to\": 906}, {\"ngram\": \"an X\", \"from\": 911, \"to\": 915}, {\"ngram\": \"a Y chromosome\", \"from\": 920, \"to\": 934}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chromosomes influence a person's sex.\", \"from\": 942, \"to\": 979, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Chromosomes influence\", \"from\": 942, \"to\": 963}, {\"ngram\": \"a person's sex\", \"from\": 964, \"to\": 978}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But hormones are important too, before birth - as well as later on during puberty.\", \"from\": 981, \"to\": 1063, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"hormones\", \"from\": 985, \"to\": 993}, {\"ngram\": \"birth\", \"from\": 1020, \"to\": 1025}, {\"ngram\": \"puberty\", \"from\": 1055, \"to\": 1062}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the baby is still growing in the womb, hormones help the reproductive organs develop.\", \"from\": 1064, \"to\": 1155, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the baby\", \"from\": 1070, \"to\": 1078}, {\"ngram\": \"the womb\", \"from\": 1099, \"to\": 1107}, {\"ngram\": \"hormones\", \"from\": 1109, \"to\": 1117}, {\"ngram\": \"the reproductive organs\", \"from\": 1123, \"to\": 1146}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, at some point through the pregnancy some babies' reproductive organs do not develop in the way most people's do.\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1278, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some point\", \"from\": 1169, \"to\": 1179}, {\"ngram\": \"the pregnancy\", \"from\": 1188, \"to\": 1201}, {\"ngram\": \"some babies' reproductive organs\", \"from\": 1202, \"to\": 1234}, {\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 1253, \"to\": 1260}, {\"ngram\": \"most people\", \"from\": 1261, \"to\": 1272}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This can be caused by conditions called DSDs: differences in sex development.\", \"from\": 1280, \"to\": 1357, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"conditions\", \"from\": 1302, \"to\": 1312}, {\"ngram\": \"DSDs\", \"from\": 1320, \"to\": 1324}, {\"ngram\": \"differences\", \"from\": 1326, \"to\": 1337}, {\"ngram\": \"sex development\", \"from\": 1341, \"to\": 1356}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are a group of about 40 conditions involving genes, hormones and reproductive organs that develop in the womb.\", \"from\": 1359, \"to\": 1475, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a group\", \"from\": 1369, \"to\": 1376}, {\"ngram\": \"about 40 conditions\", \"from\": 1380, \"to\": 1399}, {\"ngram\": \"genes\", \"from\": 1410, \"to\": 1415}, {\"ngram\": \"hormones\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1425}, {\"ngram\": \"reproductive organs\", \"from\": 1430, \"to\": 1449}, {\"ngram\": \"the womb\", \"from\": 1466, \"to\": 1474}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It means a person's sex development is different from that of most other people's.\", \"from\": 1476, \"to\": 1558, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a person's sex development\", \"from\": 1485, \"to\": 1511}, {\"ngram\": \"most other people\", \"from\": 1538, \"to\": 1555}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These chromosome abnormalities are rare - but they have come into sharp focus because of the boxing row at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1560, \"to\": 1680, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These chromosome abnormalities\", \"from\": 1560, \"to\": 1590}, {\"ngram\": \"sharp focus\", \"from\": 1626, \"to\": 1637}, {\"ngram\": \"the boxing row\", \"from\": 1649, \"to\": 1663}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1667, \"to\": 1679}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both fighters were said to have failed International Boxing Association gender eligibility tests last year - but there has been conflicting information whether XY chromosomes or elevated testosterone were found.\", \"from\": 1682, \"to\": 1893, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1721, \"end\": 1753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.231527710316927e-28, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 1842, \"end\": 1856, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"XY chromosomes\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Both fighters\", \"from\": 1682, \"to\": 1695}, {\"ngram\": \"conflicting information\", \"from\": 1810, \"to\": 1833}, {\"ngram\": \"elevated testosterone\", \"from\": 1860, \"to\": 1881}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While representatives of the fighters and the IOC insist the fighters were \\\"born women, raised as women and always competed as women\\\", critics, including some of their opponents at Paris 2024, have speculated that perhaps the fighters have DSD.\", \"from\": 1895, \"to\": 2139, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1941, \"end\": 1944, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3619516232971095e-33, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2135, \"end\": 2138, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"score\": 0.8135295012280547, \"rank\": 0.22921172310346108, \"text\": \"DSD\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"representatives\", \"from\": 1901, \"to\": 1916}, {\"ngram\": \"the fighters\", \"from\": 1920, \"to\": 1932}, {\"ngram\": \"the fighters\", \"from\": 1952, \"to\": 1964}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"born women\", \"from\": 1970, \"to\": 1981}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 1993, \"to\": 1998}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 2022, \"to\": 2027}, {\"ngram\": \"critics\", \"from\": 2030, \"to\": 2037}, {\"ngram\": \"their opponents\", \"from\": 2057, \"to\": 2072}, {\"ngram\": \"Paris\", \"from\": 2076, \"to\": 2081}, {\"ngram\": \"the fighters\", \"from\": 2117, \"to\": 2129}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Because these genetic variations are so many and so varied, some experts say it's impossible to establish that everyone with a Y chromosome is a male and everyone without a Y chromosome is a female.\", \"from\": 2141, \"to\": 2339, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these genetic variations\", \"from\": 2149, \"to\": 2173}, {\"ngram\": \"some experts\", \"from\": 2201, \"to\": 2213}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 2252, \"to\": 2260}, {\"ngram\": \"a Y chromosome\", \"from\": 2266, \"to\": 2280}, {\"ngram\": \"a male\", \"from\": 2284, \"to\": 2290}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 2295, \"to\": 2303}, {\"ngram\": \"a Y chromosome\", \"from\": 2312, \"to\": 2326}, {\"ngram\": \"a female\", \"from\": 2330, \"to\": 2338}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Just looking at the presence of a Y chromosome on its own does not answer the question of whether someone is male or female,\\\" says Prof Alun Williams, who researches genetic factors related to sport performance at the Manchester Metropolitan University Institute of Sport.\", \"from\": 2341, \"to\": 2614, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2478, \"end\": 2491, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alun_Williams\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alun Williams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alun_Williams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alun_Williams\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the presence\", \"from\": 2358, \"to\": 2370}, {\"ngram\": \"a Y chromosome\", \"from\": 2374, \"to\": 2388}, {\"ngram\": \"the question\", \"from\": 2416, \"to\": 2428}, {\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2447}, {\"ngram\": \"genetic factors\", \"from\": 2508, \"to\": 2523}, {\"ngram\": \"sport performance\", \"from\": 2535, \"to\": 2552}, {\"ngram\": \"the Manchester Metropolitan University Institute\", \"from\": 2556, \"to\": 2604}, {\"ngram\": \"Sport\", \"from\": 2608, \"to\": 2613}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's obviously a very good marker, as most people with a Y chromosome are male\\u2026but it's not a perfect indicator.\\\"\", \"from\": 2616, \"to\": 2730, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a very good marker\", \"from\": 2632, \"to\": 2650}, {\"ngram\": \"most people\", \"from\": 2655, \"to\": 2666}, {\"ngram\": \"a Y chromosome\", \"from\": 2672, \"to\": 2686}, {\"ngram\": \"a perfect indicator\", \"from\": 2709, \"to\": 2728}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For some people with DSD, the Y chromosome is not a fully formed typical male Y chromosome.\", \"from\": 2732, \"to\": 2823, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2753, \"end\": 2756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"score\": 0.8135295012280547, \"rank\": 0.22921172310346108, \"text\": \"DSD\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some people\", \"from\": 2736, \"to\": 2747}, {\"ngram\": \"the Y chromosome\", \"from\": 2758, \"to\": 2774}, {\"ngram\": \"a fully formed typical male Y chromosome\", \"from\": 2782, \"to\": 2822}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It may have some genetic material missing, damaged or swapped with the X chromosome, depending on the variation.\", \"from\": 2824, \"to\": 2936, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some genetic material\", \"from\": 2836, \"to\": 2857}, {\"ngram\": \"the X chromosome\", \"from\": 2891, \"to\": 2907}, {\"ngram\": \"the variation\", \"from\": 2922, \"to\": 2935}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When it comes to being male or female, what is usually crucial is a specific gene called SRY - which stands for 'sex-determining region of the Y chromosome'.\", \"from\": 2938, \"to\": 3095, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a specific gene\", \"from\": 3004, \"to\": 3019}, {\"ngram\": \"SRY\", \"from\": 3027, \"to\": 3030}, {\"ngram\": \"sex-determining region\", \"from\": 3051, \"to\": 3073}, {\"ngram\": \"the Y chromosome\", \"from\": 3077, \"to\": 3093}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is what is called the make-male gene.\", \"from\": 3097, \"to\": 3140, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the make-male gene\", \"from\": 3121, \"to\": 3139}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's the master switch of sex development,\\\" says Dr Emma Hilton, a developmental biologist who studies genetic disorders.\", \"from\": 3141, \"to\": 3262, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3193, \"end\": 3197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"score\": 0.9982065348714207, \"rank\": 0.0017966841649124507, \"text\": \"Emma\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\"}, {\"begin\": 3198, \"end\": 3204, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hilton_Worldwide\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8878718190396046e-15, \"text\": \"Hilton\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hilton_Worldwide\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hilton_Worldwide\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the master switch\", \"from\": 3146, \"to\": 3163}, {\"ngram\": \